         <ddi:abstract xml:lang="en">The SurMob2018 study collected data among 1273 inhabitants of Suriname. The survey covered the following topics:
•	Social background, including ethnicity and migration. These items include all compulsory social background variables of the International Social Survey Programme and more.
•	Social mobility, i.c. education and first and most recent occupations of respondent and current/last occupation of partner, as well as education and occupation of father and mother of the respondent (at age 12).
•	Migration module on siblings of respondent, including age of migration, country of destination, education and first &amp; most recent occupations of four brothers/sisters of the respondent. 
•	Attitudes on role of government (60 items) and social networks (60 items), covering the 2016 Role of Government V and 2017 Social Networks III modules of the International Social Survey Programme.</ddi:abstract>
